The paper deals with probabilistic databases and their query processing, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also proposes efficient techniques based on search algorithms from constraint satisfaction, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of computing exact tuple confidence values is a machine learning problem, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.LG). The paper also discusses problem decomposition methods and heuristics, which are techniques commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes efficient algorithms for solving the conditioning problem, which is a computational complexity problem, and thus falls under computational complexity (cs.CC).
